        "content": "<p>Say I have something like this</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Julia\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BigUnion</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Union</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Int</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Float32</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"kt\">Wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">S</span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"kt\">S</span>\n<span class=\"k\">end</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">::</span><span class=\"kt\">Wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">Int</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c\"># just for clarity</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is there an efficient way to \"upgrate\" <code>w</code> to a <code>Wrapper{BigUnion}</code>instead?<br>\nI've been rebuilding the whole object like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Julia\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">w_union</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"kt\">BigUnion</span><span class=\"p\">}(</span><span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but I'm curious to know if there is another way</p>",
